# Database Schema Structure

This guide outlines where database schema is defined and what files need to be updated when making schema changes.

## Type Definitions

The Supabase database types are defined in ](mdc:types/supabase.ts). When adding or modifying tables or columns, this file should be updated first to ensure type safety throughout the application.

Example of a table definition:
```typescript
escapes_data: {
  Row: {
    country: string;
    created_at: string;
    id: number;
    image: string;
    link: string;
    price: string;
    subtitle: string;
    title: string;
    type: "hotel" | "flight" | "hotel+flight";
    validFrom: string | null;
    validTo: string | null;
  };
  // Insert and Update definitions...
}
```

## Data Access Layer

The data fetching logic that interacts with the datab/actions/fetchEscapes.ts](mdc:app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts) - Server actions for fetching escape data

When adding new fields or tables, ensure corresponding EscapeData type is updated here:

```typescript
export type EscapeData = {
  id: number;
  created_at: string;
  // ... other fields
  type: "hotel" | "flight" | "hotel+flight" | null;
  // ... 
};
```

## Form Components

Form components that create or update daa changes:

- [app/admin/escapes/components/Escappes/components/EscapeForm.tsx) - Form component for creating/editing escapes
- [app/admin/escapes/actions.ts](mdc:app/admin/escapes/actions.ts) - Server actions for creating/updating escapes

Important patterns to update in actions.ts:
1. Form schema validation (using Zod)
2. Data transformation between form and database
3. Error handling

```typescript
// Example of schema validation
const escapeFormSchema = z.object({
  // ... other fields
  type: dealTypeEnum, // z.enum(["hotel", "fli);
```

## Display Components

Components that display database content need updates when schema changes:

- [components/escapes/s/escapes/EscapeGrid.tsx) - Gronents

The application uses differape data with various styles:

- [app/components/cards/CardSelector.tsx](mdc:app/components/cards/CardSelector.tsx) - Logic for selecting which type of card to render based on escape properties
- [app/components/cards/StandardCard.tsx](mdc:app/components/cards/StandardCard.tsx) - Default card style for regular escapes
- [app/components/cards/FeaturedCard.tsx](mdc:app/components/cards/FeaturedCard.tsx) - Enhanced card style for featured escapes with blue styling
- [app/components/cards/HotDealCard.tsx](mdc:app/components/cards/HotDealCard.tsx) - Special card style for hot deals with accent colors and flame icons

When adding new fields to the database schema, all card components need to be checked and potentially updated to display the new data properly.

## Schema Change Checklist

When modifying the database schema:

1. Update Supabase type definitions in [types/supabase.ts](mdc:types/supabase.ts)
2. Update EscapeData type in [app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts](mdc:app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts)
3. Update form validation in [app/admin/escapes/actions.ts](mdc:app/admin/escapes/actions.ts)
4. Update form components in [app/admin/escapes/components/EscapeForm.tsx](mdc:app/admin/escapes/components/EscapeForm.tsx)
5. Update all card components in [app/components/cards](mdc:app/components/cards) directory
6. Test form submission and display with the new schema